28/05/2003
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The European Commission (EC) will give Romania a brief grace period for enforcing environmental and water quality standards, the EC resident office in Bucharest announced on Tuesday (27 May). 
According to data from the EC and the Romanian government, the EU plans to allocate 1.6 billion euros to related projects, much of it in the form of grants. 
(Rompres - 28/05/03)
